featured_reviews.review_id: It's one of the 2 mosque in sector area of Bokaro Steel City. Very spacious and Greenfield aura of the place. The mosque has 2 floors and also the open area of the mosque is user for prayers during Jumma (Friday Prayers)  and during the holy month of Ramadan.  The mosque committee  are very nice people and one speciality of this mosque is that no donation has ever been asked outstation. Whatever people donate who visit with their own wish has been used to build and renovate the mosque periodically.  A madarsa is also run in the mosque premises and around 50 students receive education and become hafiz and maulana.  Very good space for parking and wuzu water and space is beautiful with fishes in the area.  RO water for drinking is provided and chilled in summer.  ACs are installed for chilling environment in summer.  In jumma, little shops like in fair come serving chicken biryani, bakery product,books,caps, toys ,ballons, ice creams, fruits, etc and even  trampolin for kids to play. Great experience whenever I visit.

featured_reviews.review_id:
One of the best and pious place to visit in such a small town like Dugda. This place is peaceful and calm . This temple was established by Khadeswari Baba.
There is a special place for marriages. Different festivals are even celebrated with full enthusiasm. During new year , this place turns into a picknick spot.
